abstract: >-
  A v3.4 working paper positioning evidence-governed harness engineering as
  the control and verification layer for agentic software development. It maps
  the full software development life cycle onto a governable, auditable
  multi-agent pipeline and studies a "shared-context false pass", a correlated
  false-pass failure mode that may arise when the AI that verifies is also an
  AI sharing the producer's source or bias. It hypothesizes that multi-model
  cross-checking reduces variance but, under shared bias, may not remove
  systematic bias (a research hypothesis pending EXP-001). It proposes a
  three-layer verification architecture (mechanical gate / model panel / human
  review of evidence) and a Skill-Capitalization loop that turns each delivered
  project into a reusable, verifiable Skill. This is a working paper; core
  claims are labelled as research hypotheses pending EXP-001 / EXP-002 (no
  validated findings yet).
